text:
PURPOSE\n The purpose of conducting a “Transition Meeting” is to collar the Incoming President
and to ensure the clubs have a humble yet effective and efficient beginning. This willencourage the club to focus on their projects for the year, provide the opportunity to
bond with fellow club members, and get to know the new leadership better.

IMPORTANT NOTES\n It is MANDATORY for all clubs to complete their Transition Meeting, ON or BEFORE
the 31st of July 2025, as stipulated in the mandatory Rotaract District Citations.
Rotaract Clubs that are not hosting an installation ceremony are expected to
conduct a Transition Meeting in full alignment with the Transition Meeting Protocol
provided for the RI year 2025-26.
If a Rotaract Club is having an Installation Ceremony, we strongly advocate for
Rotaract Clubs to organize their Transition Meetings exclusively with the
involvement of club members, recognizing it as an internal club affair. Also then, It
is not recommended for clubs to extend invitations to any District Officials for these
Transition Meetings.

GENERAL NOTES\n The duration of the Transition Meeting should not exceed 1.5 hours (90 minutes)
The recommended dress code is smart casual.
Ensure that the meeting begins at the time specified on the invitations.
Recognize the presence of the dignitaries. Formal Introductions are not necessary.
When presenting the Secretary's report, ensure that the Secretary addresses the
audience with the highlights of the year in terms of projects, achievements and
other significant events, in a brief and precise manner which could be supported
with a video (optional), and NOT ONLY a video.
If invited, inform the individuals who are required to make speeches well ahead of
time along with the respective time limits and theme/topic. (In the event the DRR,
sponsoring Rotary Club or the Institution administration is represented, ensuring
that they are given the opportunity to address the audience)
Clubs are NOT allowed to take off anything from the recommended program on
this document, but any addition can be made to the agenda provided that the
meeting is conducted within the specified time limit.
Please note that the meeting minutes should be recorded.

INVITATIONS\n We encourage clubs to conduct the meeting with only the participation of club
members.
However, if the club choses to invite the following dignitaries, invitations are
mandatory to be extended by the Incoming President/Secretary a minimum of 10
days in advance.
Presidents of the sponsoring Rotary Club for the years 2024-25 and 2025-26
Youth Services Director 2024-25 of the sponsoring Rotary Club
District Rotaract Chair (DRC)
District Rotaract Representative (DRR)
Immediate Past District Rotaract Representative (IPDRR)
District Rotaract Representative Elect (DRRE)
Guide Club Coordinators of 2024-25 and 2025-26
District Youth Services Chair (DYSC), if present it is mandatory for him to be given
the opportunity to address the audience.
District Secretaries of 2024-25 and 2025-26 (upon preference)
Chancellor/ Vice Chancellor/ Institute Head/ Faculty Dean/ Department Head/
Staff Advisor (For an institute-based clubs)

PUBLIC RELATIONS AND DIGITAL PRESENTATIONS\n  All digital presentations should follow the Rotary and Rotaract Visual Guidelines.
All videos, images, and other content should be maintained at a professional level.
All introductions should display the leadership of the individual and his/her
capabilities. Refrain from sharing inside jokes that would harm one’s first
impression of him/her.
It is recommended for the meeting to be streamed live via platforms such as
Facebook, YouTube, Instagram etc.
It is encouraged to promote the incoming Board of Directors using any form of
social media through a small video clip or artwork.
Invite online media partners to provide adequate coverage for your Transition
Meeting. (optional)
Maintain Board introductions to a minimum time limit.
The District Professional Development team and District Public Relations Team
would be pleased to assist your club in providing adequate guidance on software
use for the event.
Make sure all the technical aspects are covered before starting the transition
meeting & kindly reach out to the District Professional Development Team/ Public
Relations Team for any assistance.

id: transition-007-INTRODUCTION TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS (RECOMMENDED
section: INTRODUCTION TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS (RECOMMENDED
text:
INTRODUCTION TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS (RECOMMENDED
ORDER) \n Immediate Past President
Vice President
Secretary/ Joint Secretaries
Assistant Secretary (if applicable)
Treasurer
Assistant Treasurer (if applicable)
Sergeant-at-Arms
Editor(s)
Director(s) - Club Service
Director(s) - Community Service
Director(s) - International Service
Director(s) - Professional Development
Director(s) - Other Avenues
Any other additional committee members

PROGRAM (Agenda/Schedule) \n Dignitaries take their seats at the head table.
Sergeant-at-Arms calls the house to order (Bangs the gavel once and says “I call
the house to order”) and collars the DRR (if present) and President 2024-25 and
hands him/her the gavel.
Outgoing President calls the Transition Meeting to order (Bangs the gavel on the
gong and says “I call the Transition Meeting of Rotaract Club of [Club Name] for
the year 2024-25 to order.”)
Outgoing President officially welcomes the gathering and recognizes the presence
of dignitaries as applicable.
Rotaract Formalities
National Anthem
Flag Salutation
Rotaract Invocation
Rotary Four Way Test
Rotaract Song
Secretary’s Report for 2024-25
Address by the Outgoing President
Introduction to the Incoming President
Collaring and handing over the Gavel and Charter Certificate to the Incoming
President by the Outgoing President.
Address by the Incoming President
Announcement of Board of Directors 2025-26 (Optional)
Addresses by the DRR, DRC, DYSC, Keynote Speaker, Institute Head, and sponsoring
Rotary President. (if present)
Vote of Thanks (by the Incoming Secretary)
President 2025-26 terminates the Transition Meeting (Says “I terminate the
Transition Meeting of Rotaract Club of [Club Name] for the year 2024-25 for
fellowship and refreshments,” (if refreshments are available) and bangs the gavel
on the gong once)
Fellowship

SPECIAL NOTES FOR TRANSITION MEETINGS \n If present, refrain from leaving the dignitaries idling in case they come early.
Appoint an aide (preferably the President or a Past President) to accompany them.
Refrain from inviting separate members to read out the Rotaract Formalities.
Place the head table in a position of convenience or provide an extra screen
if/when any videos or images are being projected, for their ease of viewing.
Plastic water bottles are highly discouraged hence place glasses on the head
table. Do try to avoid the use of plastic cups and switch to paper cups or
alternative environment-friendly products if/when possible.
Remember to maintain professionalism during the course of the event.

STANDARDS TO BE MAINTAINED \n Sergeant-at-Arms is responsible to maintain silence and discipline of the
members during the Transition Meeting. He/she has the authority to direct
instructions to maintain discipline and remove disturbing personnel from the
meeting.
Ensure that no one walks into the meeting during the formalities.

HEAD TABLE SEATING \n

Before Collaring
(Left to Right)
Secretary 24/25
President 25/26
DRR
President 24/25
Chief Guest
Guest of Honor (if any)
DRC

AFTER COLLARING THE PRESIDENT & INTRODUCTION OF THE
BOARD OF OFFICIALS
(Left to Right)
Secretary 25/26
President 24/25
DRR
President 25/26
Chief Guest
Guest of Honor (if any)
DRC

LIST OF DIGNITARIES WITH DESIGNATIONS \n

District Youth Services Advisor (DYSA) - PHF Rtn. PP G.S. Sylvester
District Youth Services Chair (DYSC) - Rtn. PP Shaleeka Jayalath

Immediate Past District Rotaract Representative (IPDRR) - PHF Rtr. PP Shanel Mendis

Assistant District Rotaract Representatives (ADRRs) - Rtr. PP Dulan Samarawickrama,Rtr. PP Praneeth Madusanka, Rtn. Rtr. PP Kalana Peiris, Rtr. PP Yasiru Athugaldura Arachchi
